text:
="preserve">Mamye Edmondson BaCote (February 18, 1939 – December 14, 2020) was an American politician. She was a member of the Democratic Party. She was a member of the Virginia House of Delegates, representing the 95th District from 2004 to 2016. BaCote was born in Halifax, Virginia.
BaCote died on December 14, 2020 in Newport News, Virginia at the age of 81.
